      • data

        public SELF data(org.dbunit.dataset.IDataSet dataSet)
        Run a specified DBUnit dataset.

        This method of data insertion should be prefered instead of Unitils' DataSet annotation. By using this method your data-sets are rendered in the JGiven report, while otherwise they would not.

        Internally, uses the default DataSetLoadStrategy and DataSetFactory. These may be configured via the unitils.properties configuration file. This is explained in more detail in Configuring the dataset load strategy section of Unitils' Database Tutorial.

        Parameters:
        dataSet - a DBUnit dataset object
        Returns:
        StageBase.self()
        See Also:
        DbUnitExModule.insertDataSet(IDataSet)
